Description:
WHO ARE WE?
Join us to make a difference for the next generation and have real, tangible impact. At the intersection of education, technology, and play, Zorbit's Math by Carnegie Learning is a social enterprise that is laser-focused on making the lives of students better, paying particular attention to supporting students who are too often marginalized. People who work here wake up each morning knowing that they are having a significant positive impact on the world every day. Zorbit’s Math is a play-based learning platform for K-3 math that empowers teachers to elevate lesson plans in class, at home, and anywhere in between. We work with many of the biggest school districts in Canada, and are poised for significant growth through 2022 and beyond.
WHO ARE WE LOOKING FOR?
We are looking for a driven and passionate Marketing Manager to join our team to help us analyze, create and drive our marketing strategies. In this role you need to be a big picture strategic thinker who also isn’t afraid of getting into the finer details. Reporting to the Director of Marketing, this person will also need to fit right in with our highly entrepreneurial and driven team, and be able to appreciate a Dad joke every now and then.
*
WHY WORK HERE?
We have some awesome perks that are listed below, but the reason you’ll really want to work here is because every one of our team members is awesome and driven by the positive impact that we all get to have on children’s lives each and every day. Everyone is talented and hardworking, while also being warm, supportive, and compassionate.
As an employer, we take the approach that employees have the flexibility to design and organize their own work day to create balance between their work life and their personal/home life. This is a place for people who really thrive on freedom and autonomy. We trust you to make decisions that will maximize both your happiness, and your ability to drive our mission. We ultimately want you to be the best version of you!
Some of those perks we mentioned:
A competitive base salary;
Bonus structure;
Support of work-life balance through remote work and workday flexibility;
RRSP matching program;
Social events and celebrations;
Mission-driven culture;
Cost-shared health and dental;
3 weeks paid vacation;
Wonderful teammates (did we mention that one already?).
WHAT WILL YOU BE DOING?
Ultimately, this role will assist with driving and executing all marketing strategies and campaign management;
Drive marketing value delivery with an entrepreneurial mindset and data-driven process;
Assist with development and implementation of annual marketing plan and strategies, highlighting key campaigns, milestones, budgets, and long-term goals;
Work collaboratively with multiple teams including art (for creative and content design), educational writer (for educational content) and execution team (to execute campaigns) to help develop and drive strategy.
Drive the company’s digital strategies, and manage integrated digital programs, SEO, paid search (PPC), remarketing, and digital advertising, as well as the digital technology stack;
Responsible for programs, systems, and processes to deliver highly optimized websites for demand generation, customer success, and brand awareness;
Build an amazing customer experience and best-in-class capabilities for driving new prospects through content, personalization, and segmentation, and converting them to qualified leads;
Lead the approach for data collection, reporting, and analysis for digital marketing activities;
Oversee the full application stack including; social media, Salesforce, Pardot, Pendo and Company website;
Evaluate and implement new marketing technologies;
Lead email marketing initiatives, including workflow development and template writing to maximize open and click rates;
Liaise with distribution partners to facilitate new lead generation and the sales process.
REQUIREMENTS
Previously demonstrated experience in marketing roles, preferably in a lead marketing role in a B2B or SaaS company;
Exceptional leadership skills;
Extremely resourceful and proactive in identifying problems and finding solutions;
Outstanding verbal and written communication skills;
Ability and desire to work on big picture strategic thinking and to roll up your sleeves and get into the details;
Comfortable working in a fast-paced and growing organization;
Entrepreneurial spirit - willing to experiment, test new processes, and adapt quickly;
Highly collaborative - demonstrated ability to work exceptionally well in teams.
We recognize that there are significant institutional barriers to equity and inclusion in both classrooms and tech companies such as ours. We are an anti-racist company that seeks to act consciously to help break down those barriers. Moreover, we recognize that to deliver inclusive products and services to the teachers and young children who engage with us and our technology, we must have a diverse and inclusive staff. To that end, we are more than an equal opportunity employer - we consciously seek to make hires that increase the diversity of our staff.
LOCATION
This position is based in St. John’s, NL with the opportunity to work remotely.
